r%20Babajide%20Sanwo-Olu%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20has%20just%20been%20re-elected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESanwo-Olu%20was%20sworn%20in%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.premiumtimesng.com%2Fregional%2Fssouth-west%2F601191-breaking-sanwo-olu-sworn-in-for-second-term.html%5C%22%3Eend%20of%20May%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Part%20of%20his%20agenda%20for%20his%20new%20term%20is%20focused%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.premiumtimesng.com%2Fnews%2Fmore-news%2F601474-inauguration-sanwo-olu-sets-themes-plus-agenda-for-second-term.html%5C%22%3Etraffic%3C%2Fa%3E%20management.%20Recent%20evidence%20suggests%20that%20traffic%20jams%20are%20getting%20worse%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vanguardngr.com%2F2023%2F06%2Fmother-of-all-traffic-motorists-spend-seven-hours-in-lagos-ibadan-expressway-gridlock%5C%22%3Ewith%20or%20without%20okadas%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20survey%20we%20conducted%20found%20that%20the%20ban%20was%20very%20unpopular.%20In%20an%20ongoing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebritishacademy.ac.uk%2Fprojects%2Fhumanities-social-sciences-tackling-global-challenges-inclusive-poverty-reduction%2F%5C%22%3Eproject%3C%2Fa%3E%20undertaken%20with%20our%20colleagues%20Basirat%20Oyalowo%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscholar.google.com%2Fcitations%3Fpli%3D1%26authuser%3D1%26user%3D-GYUM9cAAAAJ%5C%22%3Eat%20the%20University%20of%20Lagos%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Eghosa%20Igudia%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dmu.ac.uk%2Fabout-dmu%2Facademic-staff%2Fbusiness-and-law%2Feghosa-igudia%2Feghosa-igudia.aspx%5C%22%3EDe%20Montfort%20University%3C%2Fa%3E%20we%20surveyed%20over%201%2C700%20people%20in%20Lagos%20in%202022.%20Around%2072%25%20disagreed%20or%20strongly%20disagreed%20that%20the%20ban%20was%20in%20the%20public%20interest.%20The%20authorities%20had%20announced%20they%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpunchng.com%2Fokada-ban-begins-today-lagos-deploys-more-boats%2F%5C%22%3Epublic%20support%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20most%20Lagosians%20for%20the%20okada%20bans%20when%20they%20were%20first%20announced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20collected%20data%20in%20August%202022%2C%20after%20the%20first%20ban%2C%20people%20surveyed%20highlighted%20the%20lack%20of%20transport%20alternatives%2C%20notably%20for%20riders%20to%20earn%20money%20and%20for%20passengers%20to%20navigate%20the%20terrible%20traffic.%20Bans%20tend%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1177%2F0308518X221083989%5C%22%3Eopposed%20or%20ignored%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20they%20cause%20inconvenience%20and%20disruption%2C%20or%20worsen%20poverty%20and%20inequality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20now%20helping%20local%20people%20develop%20alternatives%20to%20outright%20bans%20so%20that%20there%20could%20be%20better%20transport%20options.%20We%20are%20presenting%20these%20ideas%20to%20policymakers.%20These%20suggestions%20include%20establishing%20a%20way%20to%20get%20the%20public%20more%20involved%20in%20decision%20making%2C%20including%20a%20permanent%20forum%20bringing%20together%20policymakers%2C%20security%20officers%20and%20people%20working%20in%20the%20informal%20economy%2C%20such%20as%20okada%20riders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERespondents%20also%20told%20us%20they%20want%20the%20government%20to%20create%20alternative%20job%20opportunities%20for%20riders%20before%20they%20are%20affected%20by%20any%20bans%20or%20restrictions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20propose%20providing%20adequate%20and%20affordable%20transport%20alternatives%20for%20those%20previously%20using%20okadas%20to%20get%20around%3B%20and%20that%20politicians%20regularly%20monitor%20the%20effects%20these%20measures%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdora.dmu.ac.uk%2Fhandle%2F2086%2F22991%5C%22%3Eare%20having%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F535052%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20230630-23-ub4u9t.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26q%3D45%26auto%3Dformat%26w%3D1000%26fit%3Dclip%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(min-width%3A%201466px)%20754px%2C%20(max-width%3A%20599px)%20100vw%2C%20(min-width%3A%20600px)%20600px%2C%20237px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F535052%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20230630-23-ub4u9t.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26q%3D45%26auto%3Dformat%26w%3D754%26fit%3Dclip%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Drivers%20on%20their%20motorcycles%20in%20Lagos.%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F535052%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20230630-23-ub4u9t.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D45%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D400%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D1%20600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F535052%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20230630-23-ub4u9t.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D30%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D400%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D2%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F535052%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20230630-23-ub4u9t.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D15%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D400%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D3%201800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F535052%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20230630-23-ub4u9t.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D45%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D503%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D1%20754w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F535052%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20230630-23-ub4u9t.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D30%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D503%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D2%201508w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F535052%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20230630-23-ub4u9t.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D15%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D503%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D3%202262w%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMotorcycle%20taxis%20are%20controversial%20in%20Lagos.%20ariyo%20olasunkanmi%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fprofile%2FVanessa-Watson-2%2Fpublication%2F228890337_Conflicting_rationalities_Implications_for_planning_theory_and_ethics%2Flinks%2F5b1a729faca272021cf2d0da%2FConflicting-rationalities-Implications-for-planning-theory-and-ethics.pdf%5C%22%3Econtinued%20debate%20%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20okadas%20has%20created%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Fpdf%2F10.1177%2F0308518X221083989%5C%22%3Ea%20tension%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20the%20everyday%20lives%20of%20citizens%20and%20the%20authorities%E2%80%99%20vision%20for%20Lagos%20as%20a%20modern%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlternatives%20cause%20problems%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20the%20ban%2C%20some%20former%20okada%20riders%20have%20turned%20to%20driving%20keke%20marwa.%20These%20are%20also%20vulnerable%20to%20coming%20off%20badly%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthenationonlineng.net%2Fthe-keke-marwa-menace-lagosians-lament-recklessness-of-three-wheeler-vehicles%2F%5C%22%3Eroad%20traffic%20accidents%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20are%20not%20as%20able%20to%20cope%20with%20narrow%20streets%20as%20motorcycles.%20Road%20accidents%20remain%20high%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.alimoshotoday.com%2Falimosho-news%2Ftragic-lagos-records-78-cases-of-road-accidents-in-january-26-deaths-6522120%5C%22%3Egenerally%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20despite%20the%20okada%20ban.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20casualty%20statistics%20presented%20in%20support%20of%20the%20okada%20ban%20have%20been%20criticised%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.premiumtimesng.com%2Ffeatures-and-interviews%2F376896-fact-check-are-okadas-responsible-for-over-10000-accidents-in-lagos.html%3Ftztc%3D1%5C%22%3Elocal%20journalists%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20not%20being%20accurate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELagos%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Farticle%2F10.1007%2Fs10611-019-09878-x%5C%22%3Estate%20governor%20Babatunde%20Fashola%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20wanted%20to%20completely%20ban%20okadas%20in%202010%2C%20but%20compromised%20on%20banning%20them%20from%20about%205%25%20of%20Lagos%E2%80%99s%20roads.%20An%20outright%20ban%20was%20imposed%20on%20okadas%20from%20six%20of%20parts%20of%20Lagos%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fleadership.ng%2Fexamining-lagos-state-5th-okada-ban%2F%5C%22%3Ein%20June%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20followed%20by%20bans%20in%20a%20further%20four%20areas%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nigeriainfo.fm%2Fnews%2Fhomepagelagos%2Flagos-extends-okada-ban-to-10-more-lgs-lcdas%2F%5C%22%3Ein%20September%202022%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Discussions%20with%20local%20colleagues%20suggest%20that%20some%20were%20areas%20with%20particularly%20bad%20traffic%20and%20dense%20populations.%20Others%2C%20however%2C%20were%20areas%20where%20middle-class%20voters%20appear%20to%20have%20lobbied%20for%20inclusion%20in%20the%20ban.%20One%20motivation%20for%20this%20probably%20was%20concern%20over%20noise%20rather%20than%20traffic%20jams%20or%20criminality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20help%20replace%20okadas%2C%20in%20May%202021%20Sanwo-Olu%20launched%20a%20fleet%20of%20500%20minibuses%2C%20billed%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnairametrics.com%2F2021%2F05%2F19%2Flagos-launches-500-first-and-last-mile-buses-as-alternative-to-okada%2F%5C%22%3Efirst%20and%20last%20mile%20buses%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20with%20a%20plan%20to%20expand%20these%20to%205%2C000.%20Even%20if%20that%20figure%20is%20reached%2C%20these%20numbers%20cannot%20match%20the%20number%20of%20displaced%20okadas.%20And%20these%20minibuses%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20flexibility%20of%20the%20okadas%20they%20are%20intended%20to%20replace%20to%20nip%20in%20and%20out%20of%20Lagos%E2%80%99s%20narrow%20streets%20and%20past%20jams.%20On%20a%20visit%20to%20Lagos%20in%20April%202023%2C%20the%20UK%20researchers%20saw%20hardly%20any%20of%20these%20new%20buses%2C%20but%20the%20old%20danfo%20(private%20minibus)%20and%20keke%20marwa%20were%20still%20there%20in%20great%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInjuries%20and%20deaths%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20decade%20in%20particular%2C%20okadas%20have%20been%20a%20source%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1080%2F15389588.2019.1663346%5C%22%3Einjury%20and%20death%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20roads%2C%20with%20some%20riders%20also%20accused%20of%20exploiting%20the%20manoeuvrability%20of%20the%20motorcycles%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tvcnews.tv%2F2022%2F05%2Fmajority-of-okada-riders-are-criminals-in-disguise-lagos-cp%2F%5C%22%3Ecommit%20crimes%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20they%20have%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fiafoundation.org%2Fresources%2Fthe-wheels-of-change-safe-and-sustainable-motorcycles-in-sub-saharan-africa%5C%22%3Eprovided%20an%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20people%20and%20enabled%20millions%20of%20citizens%20to%20navigate%20the%20vast%20metropolis%20fairly%20swiftly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ban%20has%20hit%20the%20riders%E2%80%99%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fglobal-development%2F2022%2Foct%2F21%2Flagos-motorcycle-taxi-okada-ban-leaves-drivers-destitute%5C%22%3Eability%20to%20earn%20money%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20also%20affected%20the%20millions%20who%20previously%20were%20using%20okadas%20to%20get%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20arguments%20for%20banning%20okadas%20was%20their%20use%20by%20criminals.%20One%20of%20our%20interviewees%20reported%20that%20in%20an%20earlier%20court%20case%2C%20the%20judge%20said%20that%20the%20authorities%20should%20identify%20and%20apprehend%20criminals%2C%20rather%20than%20assuming%20that%20all%20riders%20were%20criminals%20or%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fread.dukeupress.edu%2Fpublic-culture%2Farticle%2F34%2F1%2520(96)%2F123%2F296690%5C%22%3Ecould-be%20criminals%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECriminals%20cannot%20simply%20be%20identified%20as%20those%20who%20ride%20a%20motorcycle%2C%20nor%20can%20the%20authorities%20ban%20every%20mode%20of%20transport%20that%20criminals%20exploit.%20Motorcycles%20are%20used%20widely%20in%20sub-Saharan%20Africa%20as%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20the%20transport%20system%20%E2%80%93%20the%20challenge%20is%20to%20maximise%20their%20benefits%20while%20managing%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fiafoundation.org%2Fresources%2Fthe-wheels-of-change-safe-and-sustainable-motorcycles-in-sub-saharan-africa%5C%22%3Eminimising%20their%20downsides%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20research%20confirms%20that%20okada%20riders%20and%20those%20who%20used%20okadas%20view%20such%20their%20use%20as%20a%20legitimate%20source%20of%20income%2C%20this%20is%20particularly%20relevant%20in%20a%20country%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fworldpoverty.io%2Fmap%5C%22%3Elargest%20number%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20people%20living%20in%20extreme%20poverty%20in%20the%20world%20(over%2071%20million).%20Meanwhile%2C%20as%20Nigeria%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flagossdgandinvestment.com%2Fglancelagos%5C%22%3Eeconomic%20powerhouse%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Lagos%20continues%20to%20draw%20in%20people%20from%20across%20Nigeria%20and%20beyond%2C%20and%20informal%20economic%20activities%20such%20as%20okada%20riding%20have%20helped%20to%20absorb%20these%20individuals%20into%20the%20economy%20of%20Lagos.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20little%20evidence%20of%20improvement%20in%20the%20general%20traffic%20situation%20in%20Lagos%20because%20of%20the%20ban.%20Poverty%20remains%20widespread%2C%20the%20motorcycle%20taxi%20ban%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20make%20that%20worse%20as%20people%20struggle%20to%20find%20affordable%2C%20accessible%20transport%20and%20others%20are%20denied%20the%20opportunity%20to%20provide%20that.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F207374%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Frobert-ackrill-114323%5C%22%3ERobert%20Ackrill%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Professor%20of%20European%20Economics%20and%20Policy%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Fnottingham-trent-university-1338%5C%22%3ENottingham%20Trent%20University%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Folasunmbo-olusanya-1455707%5C%22%3EOlasunmbo%20Olusanya%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Senior%20Lecturer%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Funiversity-of-lagos-1959%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Lagos%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Ftraffic-jams-are-overwhelming-africas-biggest-city-heres-what-could-help-207374%5C%22%3Eoriginal%20article%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690615824000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F29124225%2F1024px-Oshodi_Lagos_01.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Ftraffic-jams-overwhelm-africas-biggest-city-informal-public-transport-may-be-a-solution%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%202023%2C%20Lagos%20was%20ranked%20the%20fourth%20most%20uncomfortable%20city%20to%20live%20in%20in%20the%20world%20partly%20because%20of%20this.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Ftraffic-jams-overwhelm-africas-biggest-city-informal-public-transport-may-be-a-solution%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'No%20Material'%20to%20Demonstrate%20Terror%20Link%2C%20Yet%20Vernon%20Gonsalves%2C%20Arun%20Ferriera%20Spent%205%20Years%20in%20Jail%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F28135451%2FUntitled-design-20-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20It%20took%20five-full%20years%20of%20incarceration%20and%20several%20rejections%20of%20bail%20applications%20before%20both%20the%20trial%20court%20and%20the%20high%20court%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20finally%20could%20notice%20that%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20premier%20investigating%20agency%2C%20the%20National%20Investigations%20Agency%20(NIA)%2C%20has%20shown%20no%20evidence%20to%20keep%20two%20men%20in%20their%20custody.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Friday%2C%20July%2028%2C%20in%20a%20detailed%2054-page%20bail%20order%20observed%20that%20human%20rights%20defenders%20Vernon%20Gonsalves%20and%20Arun%20Ferriera%20were%20both%20held%20in%20jail%20even%20when%20%E2%80%9Cno%20material%20has%20been%20demonstrated%20by%20the%20NIA%20before%20us%20that%20the%20appellants%20are%20members%20of%20the%20terrorist%20organisation%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Felgar-parishad-bail-vernon-gonsalves-arun-ferreira-supreme-court%5C%22%3EAfter%205%20Years%20in%20Jail%2C%20Vernon%20Gonsalves%20and%20Arun%20Ferreira%20Get%20Bail%20in%20Elgar%20Parishad%20Case%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20significant%20observation%20coming%20from%20the%20top%20court%20of%20the%20country%20in%20a%20case%20where%2016%20human%20rights%20defenders%20and%20academics%20have%20suffered%20prolonged%20incarceration%20under%20highly%20questionable%20claims.%20The%20Elgar%20Parishad%20case%2C%20registered%20by%20the%20Pune%20police%20in%202018%2C%20when%20Devendra%20Fadnavis%20was%20Maharashtra%E2%80%99s%20chief%20minister%20and%20later%20handed%20over%20to%20the%20NIA%20soon%20after%20the%20BJP%20government%20fell%20in%20the%20state%20in%202020%2C%20has%20raised%20several%20pertinent%20questions%20about%20the%20credibility%20of%20the%20police%E2%80%99s%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F21200002%2FScreen-Shot-2021-04-21-at-7.59.46-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22770%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F21200002%2FScreen-Shot-2021-04-21-at-7.59.46-PM.png%20770w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F21200002%2FScreen-Shot-2021-04-21-at-7.59.46-PM-300x168.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-524045%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22431%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%2016%20arrested%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20Elgar%20Parishad%20case.%20One%20of%20them%2C%20Father%20Stan%20Swamy%2C%20passed%20away%20in%20custody.%20Photo%3A%20The%20Wire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGonsalves%20and%20Ferriera%20have%20been%20in%20custody%20since%20August%202018.%20The%20prosecution%20has%20charged%20the%20two%2C%20like%20the%2014%20others%20in%20the%20case%2C%20under%20the%20draconian%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20(UAPA).%20According%20to%20the%20chargesheet%20filed%20by%20the%20Pune%20police%20and%20later%20adopted%20by%20the%20NIA%2C%20Gonsalves%20and%20Ferriera%20had%20allegedly%20played%20an%20important%20role%20in%20%E2%80%9Crecruiting%E2%80%9D%20young%20people%20into%20the%20banned%20CPI%20(Maoist)%20organisation.%20Ferriera%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20this%2C%20had%20allegedly%20handled%20the%20funds%20related%20to%20the%20organisation%E2%80%99s%20activities%2C%20more%20specifically%2C%20in%20the%20urban%20regions%20%E2%80%93%20which%20the%20prosecution%20terms%20as%20%E2%80%9CUrban%20Naxal%20(-ism)%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENIA%20contentions%20and%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20observations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20division%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Aniruddha%20Bose%20and%20Sudhanshu%20Dhulia%20has%2C%20however%2C%20seen%20through%20the%20prosecution%E2%80%99s%20claims.%20The%20bail%20order%20breaks%20down%20the%20NIA%E2%80%99s%20contention%20mainly%20into%20three%20parts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scribd.com%2Fembeds%2F661800890%2Fcontent%3Fstart_page%3D1%26view_mode%3Dscroll%26access_key%3Dkey-R0f8Ditq0eHsm0VXxB08%5C%22%20tabindex%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20data-auto-height%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20data-aspect-ratio%3D%5C%220.7068965517241379%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Supreme%20Court%20Order%20on%20Vernon%20Gonsalves%20and%20Arun%20Ferriera%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scribd.com%2Fdocument%2F661800890%2FSupreme-Court-Order-on-Vernon-Gonsalves-and-Arun-Ferriera%23from_embed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22View%20Supreme%20Court%20Order%20on%20Vernon%20Gonsalves%20and%20Arun%20Ferriera%20on%20Scribd%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court%20Order%20on%20Vern%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scribd.com%2Fuser%2F286754081%2FThe-Wire%23from_embed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22View%20The%20Wire's%20profile%20on%20Scribd%5C%22%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20first%20is%20their%20association%20with%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%20which%20the%20prosecution%20claims%20from%20the%20letters%20and%20witness%20statements%E2%80%A6%20But%20what%20we%20must%20be%20conscious%20of%2C%20while%20dealing%20with%20prima%20facie%20worth%20of%20these%20statements%20and%20documents%20is%20that%20none%20of%20them%20had%20been%20seized%20or%20recovered%20from%20the%20appellants%20but%20these%20recoveries%20are%20alleged%20to%20have%20been%20made%20from%20the%20co-accused%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20points%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20head%2C%20the%20court%20states%2C%20is%20of%20the%20alleged%20offensive%20acts%20of%20keeping%20literature%20propagating%20violence%20and%20promoting%20overthrowing%20of%20a%20democratically%20elected%20government%20through%20armed%20struggle.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20again%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20states%2C%20%E2%80%9Cit%20is%20not%20the%20NIA%E2%80%99s%20case%20that%20either%20of%20the%20two%20appellants%20is%20the%20author%20of%20the%20materials%20found%20from%20their%20residences%2C%20as%20alleged.%20None%20of%20these%20literatures%20has%20been%20specifically%20proscribed%20so%20as%20to%20constitute%20an%20offence%2C%20just%20by%20keeping%20them.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThirdly%2C%20pointing%20to%20the%20prosecution%E2%80%99s%20claim%20made%20against%20Ferriera%20of%20alleged%20handling%20of%20finances%2C%20the%20apex%20court%20has%20observed%20that%2C%20%E2%80%9CBut%20such%20finances%2C%20as%20per%20the%20materials%20through%20which%20the%20dealings%20are%20sought%20to%20be%20established%2C%20show%20that%20the%20transaction%20was%20mainly%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20litigation%20on%20behalf%20of%2C%20it%20appears%20to%20us%2C%20detained%20party%20persons.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20says%2C%20at%20the%20time%20of%20rejecting%20their%20bail%20applications%2C%20the%20high%20court%20had%20not%20%E2%80%9Copined%20that%20there%20were%20reasonable%20grounds%20for%20believing%20that%20the%20accusations%20against%20such%20persons%20were%20not%20prima%20facie%20true%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%20years%2C%20the%20state%20government%20has%20termed%20several%20human%20rights%20and%20cultural%20outfits%20as%20a%20frontal%20organisation%20of%20the%20banned%20Maoist%20groups.%20In%20February%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fmaharashtra-top-cop-accuses-decades-old-cultural-rights-orgs-of-working-as-naxal-fronts%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20reported%20about%20a%20report%20by%20a%20state%20Deputy%20Inspector%20General%20of%20Police%20(DIGP)%20terming%20as%20many%20as%2015%20organisations%20as%20frontal%20outfits.%20Among%20them%20is%20the%20Indian%20Association%20of%20Peoples%20Lawyers%20(IAPL)%2C%20which%20also%20finds%20a%20mention%20in%20the%20Elgar%20Parishad%20chargesheet.%20The%20organisation%2C%20as%20the%20name%20suggests%2C%20is%20a%20loose%20network%20of%20lawyers%20working%20on%20issues%20relating%20to%20human%20rights%20violation%20across%20the%20country.%20The%20organisation%2C%20in%202021%2C%20was%20added%20to%20the%20list%20of%20%E2%80%9Cenemies%E2%80%9D%20as%20mentioned%20under%20the%20Union%20home%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fmaharashtra-activists-lawyers-union-war-book-enemies-of-state%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CUnion%20War%20Book%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20makes%20a%20few%20pertinent%20observations%20about%20the%20organisation.%20Ferriera%2C%20a%20lawyer%20by%20profession%2C%20is%20accused%20of%20being%20a%20part%20of%20the%20IAPL.%20To%20this%2C%20the%20court%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CAF%E2%80%99s%20(Ferriera%E2%80%99s)%20involvement%20with%20IAPL%20as%20a%20frontal%20organisation%20of%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Maoist)%20is%20sought%20to%20be%20established%2C%20and%20that%20has%20been%20referred%20to%20in%20the%20chargesheet%20as%20well.%20But%20the%20link%20between%20IAPL%20and%20the%20CPI%20(Maoist)%20has%20not%20been%20clearly%20demonstrated%20through%20any%20material.%E2%80%9D%20The%20judges%20have%20gone%20to%20the%20extent%20of%20giving%20a%20clean%20chit%20to%20IAPL%20by%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20reliable%20evidence%20to%20link%20IAPL%20with%20CPI%20(Maoist)%20as%20its%20frontal%20organisation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20the%20NIA%20accused%20both%20Ferriera%20and%20Gonsalves%20of%20being%20a%20member%20of%20the%20CPI%20(Maoist).%20This%20allegation%20is%20based%20on%20the%20statements%20made%20by%20the%20protected%20witness%20(mentioned%20in%20the%20chargesheet).%20The%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20however%2C%20has%20pointed%20to%20the%20link%20that%2C%20the%20NIA%20claims%2C%20was%20made%20in%20relation%20to%20events%20between%20the%20years%202002-2007.%20This%2C%20the%20court%20points%20out%2C%20was%20%E2%80%9Cbefore%20the%20organisation%20was%20included%20in%20the%20First%20Schedule%20to%20the%20(UAPA)%201967%20Act%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CNo%20evidence%20of%20continued%20membership%20after%20the%20party%20was%20classified%20as%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%20has%20been%20brought%20to%20our%20notice%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NIA%2C%20along%20with%20witnesses%2C%20has%20based%20its%20allegations%20on%20the%20letters%20and%20electronic%20evidence%20it%20claims%20to%20have%20recovered%20from%20other%20arrested%20persons%20in%20the%20case.%20These%20letters%20purportedly%20point%20to%20both%20Gonsalves%20and%20Ferriera%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20the%20Radical%20Student%20Union%20Initiative%2C%20among%20other%20%E2%80%9Cunlawful%20activities%E2%80%9D.%20The%20letters%2C%20however%2C%20have%20been%20shown%20recovered%20from%20the%20co-accused%20and%20not%20the%20duo.%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20we%20must%20be%20conscious%20of%2C%20while%20dealing%20with%20prima%20facie%20worth%20of%20these%20statements%20and%20documents%20is%20that%20none%20of%20them%20had%20been%20seized%20or%20recovered%20from%20the%20appellants%20but%20these%20recoveries%20are%20alleged%20to%20have%20been%20made%20from%20the%20co-accused.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20Gonsalves%20and%20Ferriera%2C%20only%20three%20others%20%E2%80%93%20poet%20and%20writer%20Varavara%20Rao%2C%20trade%20union%20activist%20and%20academic%20Sudha%20Bharadwaj%20and%20civil%20liberties%20activist%20and%20academic%20Anand%20Teltumbde%20%E2%80%93%20were%20released%20on%20bail.%20Among%20the%20three%2C%20only%20Teltumbde%E2%80%99s%20bail%20was%20decided%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Felgar-parishad-case-granted-bail-on-merits-the-bombay-hc-order-on-anand-teltumbde-is-significant%5C%22%3Emerit%20of%20the%20case%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Bharadwaj%E2%80%99s%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdefault%20bail%E2%80%9D%20and%20Rao%20was%20granted%20a%20medical%20bail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Felgar-parishad-case-granted-bail-on-merits-the-bombay-hc-order-on-anand-teltumbde-is-significant%5C%22%3EElgar%20Parishad%20Case%3A%20Granted%20Bail%20on%20%E2%80%98Merits%E2%80%99%2C%20Bombay%20HC%20Order%20on%20Anand%20Teltumbde%20Is%20Significant%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20relies%20on%20the%20bail%20order%20by%20the%20Bombay%20high%20court%20in%20Teltumbde%E2%80%99s%20case.%20Teltumbde%2C%20who%20was%20released%20on%20bail%20in%20November%20last%20year%2C%20was%20also%20accused%20of%20%E2%80%9Craising%20funds%E2%80%9D%20for%20work%20that%20the%20NIA%20considers%20to%20be%20a%20terrorist%20act.%20The%20NIA%20claimed%20that%20Teltumbde%20received%20Rs%2090%2C000%20from%20his%20co-accused%20and%20foremost%20rights%20lawyer%20from%20Nagpur%2C%20Surendra%20Gadling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20money%2C%20according%20to%20the%20NIA%2C%20was%20routed%20through%20Maoist%20leader%20Milind%20Teltumbde.%20Milind%2C%20also%20a%20younger%20brother%20of%20Anand%2C%20was%20killed%20in%20police%20firing%20last%20year.%20The%20high%20court%20has%20already%20found%20a%20%E2%80%9Cfallacy%20in%20the%20argument%20of%20the%20NIA%E2%80%9D.%20The%20high%20court%2C%20in%20the%20bail%20order%2C%20had%20raised%20questions%20over%20the%20credibility%20of%20the%20NIA%E2%80%99s%20claims%20and%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20too%20has%20relied%20on%20the%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20reasonings.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690615812000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F28135451%2FUntitled-design-20-2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fno-material-to-demonstrate-terror-link-yet-vernon-gonsalves-arun-ferriera-spent-5-years-in-jail%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20a%20detailed%20bail%20order%20observed%20that%20human%20rights%20defenders%20were%20both%20imprisoned%20even%20when%20'no%20material%20has%20been%20demonstrated%20by%20the%20NIA%20before%20us%20that%20the%20appellants%20are%20members%20of%20the%20terrorist%20organisation'.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fno-material-to-demonstrate-terror-link-yet-vernon-gonsalves-arun-ferriera-spent-5-years-in-jail%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Australia's%20Usman%20Khawaja%2C%20Marnus%20Labuschagne%20Script%20Bizarre%20Ashes%20Record%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAustralian%20batters%20Usman%20Khawaja%20and%20Marnus%20Labuschange%20entered%20record%20books%20for%20the%20slow%20pace%20of%20their%20batting%20during%20the%20fifth%20and%20final%20Ashes%20Test%20against%20England%20at%20The%20Oval.%20They%20batted%20at%20a%20run%20rate%20that%20created%20a%20new%20Ashes%20record.%20Khawaja%20and%20Marnus%20batted%20really%20slow%20in%20Australia's%20first%20innings%2C%20stitching%2042-run%20stand%20for%20the%20second%20wicket%20in%2026%20overs.%20This%20was%20largely%20due%20to%20Labuschagne's%20slow%20knock%20of%20nine%20runs%20in%2082%20balls.%20By%20the%20time%20Labuschagne%20was%20dismissed%2C%20Khawaja%20had%20played%20123%20balls%20and%20was%20unbeaten%20on%2037.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20partnership%20came%20at%20a%20run%20rate%20of%201.61%2C%20which%20is%20the%20lowest%20partnership%20in%20Ashes%20history%20among%20the%20pairs%20which%20faced%20a%20minimum%20of%20150%20balls%20in%20an%20innings%20together.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20broke%20the%20record%20of%20England's%20Michael%20Carberry%20and%20Joe%20Root%2C%20who%20had%20scored%20at%20a%20run%20rate%20of%201.75%20against%20Australia%20in%20Adelaide%20in%202013.%20In%20the%20second%20Test%20of%20the%20series%20back%20then%2C%20the%20duo%20stitched%20a%20stand%20of%2048%20runs%20in%20about%2027%20overs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAustralia%20were%20115%2F2%20at%20Lunch%20with%20Steve%20Smith%20and%20Usman%20Khawaja%20on%2013*%20and%2047*%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20their%20first%20innings%2C%20England%20were%20bundled%20out%20for%20283%20runs%20after%20being%20put%20to%20bat%20first%20by%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarry%20Brook%20(85%20in%2091%20balls%20with%2011%20fours%20and%20two%20sixes)%20top-scored%20for%20England%20and%20had%20a%20111-run%20stand%20with%20Moeen%20Ali%20(34%20in%2037%20balls%20with%20three%20fours%20and%20two%20sixes)%20after%20England%20slipped%20to%2073%2F3.%20A%2049-run%20stand%20for%20the%20eighth%20wicket%20between%20Mark%20Wood%20(28)%20and%20Chris%20Woakes%20(36)%20helped%20England%20reach%20a%20decent%20first-innings%20score.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMitchell%20Starc%20(4%2F82)%20was%20the%20pick%20of%20the%20bowlers%20for%20Australia.%20Josh%20Hazlewood%20and%20Todd%20Murphy%20took%20two%20wickets%20each%20while%20skipper%20Pat%20Cummins%20and%20Mitchell%20Marsh%20got%20a%20wicket%20each.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAustralia%20are%20leading%20the%20five-match%20series%202-1.%20Though%20Australia%20has%20regained%20the%20Ashes%20urn%2C%20England%20can%20still%20level%20the%20series.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(This%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20auto-generated%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690615740000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%