0Canaveral%20Space%20Force%20Base%20or%20the%20Kennedy%20Space%20Center%2C%20according%20to%20NASA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20July%2028%20at%2012%3A01%20a.m.%20ET%2C%20Falcon%209%20launched%2022%20Starlink%20satellites%20to%20low-Earth%20orbit%20from%20Space%20Launch%20Complex%2040%20(SLC-40)%20at%20Cape%20Canaveral%20Space%20Force%20Base%20in%20Florida.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPreviously%2C%20SpaceX%20launched%2054%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-starlink-satellites-internet%5C%22%3EStarlink%20satellites%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20orbit%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-falcon-9-launches-updates-schedule%5C%22%3EFalcon%209%3C%2Fa%3E%20rocket%20on%20July%2015.%20Before%20that%2C%20SpaceX%20conducted%20a%20July%209%20launch%20of%2022%20Starlink%20satellites%20into%20orbit%2C%20according%20to%20the%20SpaceX%20website.%20Two%20days%20prior%20on%20July%207th%2C%20it%20launched%2048%20Starlink%20satellites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20non-Starlink%20mission%20was%20when%20SpaceX%20launched%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-threads-rockets-european-space-agency-elon-musk-2023-7%5C%22%3EEuropean%20Space%20Agency%3C%2Fa%3E's%20Euclid%2C%20which%20is%20a%20space%20telescope%20designed%20to%20help%20map%20out%20the%20structure%20of%20the%20universe.%20It%20last%20worked%20with%20NASA%20on%20June%2030th%20when%20the%20SpaceX%20Dragon%20returned%20to%20Earth%20from%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20after%2023%20days%2C%20per%20the%20SpaceX%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpaceX%20wasn't%20always%20an%20industry%20darling.%20It%20nearly%20went%20bankrupt%20in%202008%20following%20three%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-history-biggest-moments-elon-musk-2022-12%23between-2006-and-2008-spacex-had-three-failed-launch-attempts-that-musk-has-said-almost-ended-the-company-3%5C%22%3Efailed%20SpaceX%20launch%3C%2Fa%3E%20attempts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Musk%2C%20its%20fourth%20attempt%20was%20its%20last%20chance%20at%20being%20viable%2C%20and%20it%20was%20this%20last-ditch%20effort%20that%20made%20SpaceX%20the%20first%20private%20company%20to%20achieve%20a%20successful%20orbital%20launch.%20This%20success%20encouraged%20NASA%20and%20some%20private%20investors%20to%20invest%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20funded%20the%20company%20in%20part%20with%20his%20sale%20of%20PayPal%20to%20eBay.%20He%20invested%20a%20third%20of%20his%20fortune%20into%20the%20venture%2C%20received%20%24278%20million%20from%20NASA%2C%20and%20got%20further%20funding%20from%20the%20United%20States%20Department%20of%20Defense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company's%20first%20rocket%2C%20the%20Falcon%201%2C%20cost%20%24100%20million%20to%20build.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-launch%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690600622000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62e8f53957dd3c0018dbfb4a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-launch%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20SpaceX%20launch%20history%20includes%20249%20launches%2C%20210%20landings%2C%20and%20183%20reflights%2C%20primarily%20sending%20Starlink%20satellites%20into%20space.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kyle%40ktwilson.ca%20(Kyle%20Wilson)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A62%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-launch%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22DeSantis%20board%20secures%20small%20win%20in%20feud%20against%20Disney%20after%20judge%20denies%20Florida%20park's%20request%20to%20throw%20out%20suit%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221745%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Walt%20Disney%20World%20and%20the%20Florida%20Gov.%20Ron%20DeSantis-appointed%20board%20that%20controls%20the%20district%20a