yed%20as%20blind%20%E2%80%94%20all%20for%20gags.%20In%20%3Cem%3EMujhse%20Shaadi%20Karogi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2004)%2C%20Kader%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20character%20is%20seen%20to%20have%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdifferent%20disability%E2%80%9D%20every%20day.%20The%20staff%20at%20his%20care%20facility%20trivialises%20it%20and%20portrays%20as%20%E2%80%9Cmake-believe%E2%80%9D%20that%20the%20character%20engages%20in.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeedless%20to%20say%2C%20portrayals%20of%20disability%20in%20Indian%20films%20and%20other%20media%20leave%20a%20lot%20to%20be%20desired.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20may%20say%20that%20these%20are%20just%20light-hearted%20movies%20meant%20for%20entertainment.%20But%20it%20is%20integral%20to%20acknowledge%20that%20we%20are%20at%20a%20point%20in%20history%20where%20there%20is%20a%20greater%20attempt%20to%20look%20beyond%20the%20myths%20and%20stereotypes%2C%20and%20understand%20disability%20for%20what%20it%20truly%20is.%20Reducing%20it%20to%20a%20punchline%20reinforces%20existing%20stereotypes%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20the%20viewers.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20popular%20trope%20that%20a%20number%20of%20filmmakers%20have%20engaged%20in%20is%20the%20infantilisation%20of%20people%20with%20disabilities.%20This%20can%20be%20seen%20in%20popular%20movies%20like%20%3Cem%3EKoi%20Mil%20Gaya%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2003)%20and%20%3Cem%3EBarfi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2012).%20Here%2C%20adults%20with%20disabilities%20are%20portrayed%20as%20%E2%80%9Cinnocent%E2%80%9D%20or%20even%20childlike%20in%20their%20actions%2C%20speech%2C%20or%20capabilities.%20This%20contributes%20to%20the%20belief%20that%20persons%20with%20disabilities%20always%20need%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F253449%2Fcoronavirus-resources-for-persons-with-disabilities-caregivers-covid-19-online-support-groups-job-portals-companionship-mental-health-nimhans-india-div200%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunder%20the%20care%20of%20someone%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20independent%2C%20the%20way%20one%20one%20would%20be%20with%20a%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-in-cinema-1690541530.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-in-cinema-1690541530.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-in-cinema-1690541530-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-in-cinema-1690541530-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-in-cinema-1690541530-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-in-cinema-1690541530-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-325558%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EWhile%20disability%20is%20caricaturized%20in%20Golmaal%2C%20Koi%20Mil%20Gayaa%20uses%20it%20to%20infantilize%20the%20main%20character.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20there%E2%80%99s%20the%20opposite%20route%20of%20morbidity.%20In%20%3Cem%3EGuzaarish%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2010)%2C%20we%20see%20Hrithik%20Roshan%E2%80%99s%20character%20insisting%20on%20how%20he%E2%80%99d%20rather%20die%20than%20live%20a%20long%20happy%20life%20as%20a%20person%20with%20a%20disability.%20He%20has%20a%20promising%20career%2C%20and%20a%20supportive%20community.%20Yet%20he%20is%20unable%20to%20make%20meaning%20of%20his%20life.%20Persons%20who%20have%20acquired%20a%20disability%20go%20through%20a%20whole%20course%20of%20turbulent%20emotions%2C%20ones%20that%20may%20include%20the%20feelings%20described%20above.%20Films%20like%20this%20present%20a%20rather%20morbid%20take%20and%20make%20the%20viewer%20feel%20like%20this%20is%20normal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20also%20often%20misses%20the%20mark%20is%20media%20representation%20of%20neurodiversity.%20Shows%20like%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Good%20Doctor%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20%3Cem%3EAtypical%20%3C%2Fem%3Erepresent%20neurodiversity%20in%20stereotypical%20ways.%20For%20instance%2C%20not%20every%20individual%20who%20is%20on%20the%20autism%20spectrum%20possesses%20savant%20skills.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20often%20goes%20untouched%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20autism%20is%20a%20spectrum%2C%20and%20that%20every%20autistic%20experience%20is%20unique%20and%20extremely%20individual-centric.%20Another%20bone%20of%20contention%20that%20affects%20the%20autistic%20community%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20such%20roles%20are%20played%20by%20allistic%20(non-autistic%20characters).%20Oftentimes%2C%20even%20the%20team%20of%20directors%20or%20writers%20is%20devoid%20of%20any%20person%20with%20autism%2C%20as%20was%20true%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Atypical%2C%20in%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FAtypical%2Fstatus%2F890667170266357760%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Eautistic%20representation%20could%20only%20manage%20to%20find%20a%20place%20in%20one%20of%20the%20supporting%20roles%20and%20the%20social%20media%20team%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhere%20are%20the%20PwDs%20in%20the%20writers%E2%80%99%20rooms%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20portrayals%20of%20disability%20make%20pity%20or%20sympathy%20the%20focal%20point%20of%20disability%20and%20take%20away%20from%20the%20narrative%20of%20pride%20and%20equity.%20A%20big%20reason%20why%20the%20representation%20of%20disability%20remains%20rudimentary%20is%20that%20there%20are%20very%20few%20PwDs%20in%20the%20writer%E2%80%99s%20rooms%2C%20wearing%20the%20director%E2%80%99s%20cap%2C%20or%20even%20representing%20themselves%20on%20screen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResearch%20in%20the%20United%20States%20has%20shown%20that%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2021%2F07%2F28%2Farts%2Ftelevision%2Fdisability-representation-study-film-television.html%5C%22%3E95%25%20of%20the%20characters%20with%20disabilities%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20played%20by%20actors%20without%20disabilities.%20In%20the%20USA%2C%20there%20is%20one%20person%20with%20a%20disability%20for%20every%20four%20people%2C%20but%20only%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.respectability.org%2F2019%2F11%2Fglaad-tv-report-2019%2F%5C%22%3E3.1%20percent%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20characters%20that%20are%20shown%20on-screen%20are%20disabled.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20numbers%20are%20even%20lesser%20for%20children%20with%20disabilities%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fseejane.org%2Fresearch-informs-empowers%2Fsee-jane-2019%2F%5C%22%3Eless%20than%20one%20percent%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Several%20studies%20also%20show%20that%20the%20industry%20is%20losing%20billions%20of%20dollars%20by%20not%20being%20inclusive%20%E2%80%94%20the%20spirit%C2%A0%20of%20the%20DEI%20(Disability%20Equality%20Indiex)%20has%20not%20yet%20seeped%20into%20the%20creative%20space.%20For%20instance%2C%20a%20research%20study%20by%20Ruderman%20Family%20Foundation%20found%20that%20Hollywood%20is%20incurring%20whopping%20losses%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frudermanfoundation.org%2Fwhite_papers%2Fdisability-inclusion-in-movies-and-television-market-research-2019%2F%5C%22%3E%24125%20billion%20dollars%3C%2Fa%3E%20every%20year%20by%20not%20having%20authentic%20disability%20representation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhere%20we%20make%20strides%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20disability%20representation%20in%20mainstream%20media%20is%20still%20far%20from%20authentic%2C%20it%20has%20come%20a%20long%20way%20from%20being%20restricted%20to%20characters%20that%20garner%20a%20few%20laughs%20to%20ones%20that%20foster%20compassion%20and%20are%20a%20window%20into%20the%20life%20of%20a%20person%20with%20a%20disability.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20a%20list%20of%20a%20few%20recommendations%20that%20you%20can%20indulge%20in%20this%20Disability%20Pride%20Month%20with%20your%20family.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMargarita%20with%20a%20Straw%20(2014)%20%E2%80%93%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Based%20on%20the%20book%20%3Cem%3EOne%20Little%20Finger%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20movie%20features%20Laila%2C%20a%20young%20woman%20with%20Cerebral%20Palsy%2C%20who%20goes%20to%20New%20York%20to%20pursue%20her%20education%20and%20unfurls%20a%20new%20chapter%20of%20her%20life.%20The%20movie%20beautifully%20depicts%20the%20diverse%20crossroads%20one%20finds%20themselves%20at%2C%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20friendships%20and%20relationships.%20(NC-17%20only%3A%20Not%20suitable%20for%20viewers%20under%2017%20years.)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed%20wp-block-embed-youtube%20wp-embed-aspect-16-9%20wp-has-aspect-ratio%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed__wrapper%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20data-skipgform_ajax_framebjll%20data-origheight%3D%5C%22270%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F6zy3F0WVDK0%3Fenablejsapi%3D1%26autoplay%3D0%26cc_load_policy%3D0%26cc_lang_pref%3D%26iv_load_policy%3D3%26loop%3D0%26modestbranding%3D0%26rel%3D0%26fs%3D1%26playsinline%3D0%26autohide%3D2%26theme%3Ddark%26color%3Dred%26controls%3D1%26%5C%22%20data-no-lazy%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20player%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%20data-origwidth%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22270%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECODA%20(2021)%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EChildren%20of%20Deaf%20Adults%20(CODA)%20shines%20a%20spotlight%20on%20the%20challenges%20that%20children%20of%20deaf%20adults%20experience%20%E2%80%93%20from%20being%20early%20caregivers%20to%20their%20disabled%20kin%20to%20missing%20out%20on%20the%20%E